Let's go.

253
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,280
Mr. Sonrak.

254
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:04,600
Chaiya's completely out of control.

255
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,880
He went up there and sang instead of you.

256
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,880
What the heck happened, Chang?

257
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,440
How did Chaiya get on stage and sing?

258
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:15,920
I'm surprised too.
Why is Puna even up there with him?

259
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,400
They planned it.

260
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,760
They want to make Darathong Music
look bad.

261
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:22,880
Manat.

262
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:25,640
What happened?

263
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:27,720
Well…

264
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:30,040
We were a bit late.

265
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:33,760
Ms. Praewa had to find someone
to sing instead.

266
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,000
How could they do this?

267
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:37,280
Let's hurry to the stage.

268
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:41,840
Hurry! Get them off the stage.

269
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,880
Doing this,
they've gone a bit too far.

270
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:49,680
Go fix this immediately! Now!

271
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:55,320
Serves them right!

272
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:59,000
I want to laugh in English, hehehe.

273
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:04,120
They're using us like crazy,
treating us like servants.

274
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,080
Wait, aren't we?

275
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:07,400
-No!
-Huh?

276
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,800
I work for money.

277
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,520
I'm not anyone's servant.

278
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,760
Wait, why are you taking this?

279
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,360
It's not something we need.

280
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:17,320
I'm hiding it.

281
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,400
So they can't find it.

282
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:20,760
Let's see, without the props,

283
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,640
can they even go on stage?

284
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:27,080
-You're really mischievous.
-Let's go!

285
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:35,000
I'm so fed up with Maria.
She's always bossing us around!

286
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,680
No raise for us either.

287
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,680
-This is Maria's car!
-Yes.

288
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,600
Oh! The windows aren't closed.

289
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,520
What?

290
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,000
The doors aren't locked too.

291
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,240
Perfect! We'll hide this stuff

292
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,960
-in her car.
-Okay.

293
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,440
When they search,

294
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:59,080
we can say
Maria told us to put it here.

295
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,480
She'll get scolded for once.

296
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:03,400
Perfect! Time to get our revenge.

297
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:05,840
Just put it in the back.

298
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:17,080
Wait, dear.

299
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:19,640
Go ahead. I forgot to lock the car.

300
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,200
Okay, Dad. Come quickly!

301
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,160
Bye for now.

302
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:31,960
I feel my curiosity kicking in.

303
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:35,520
I really want to know
what's in the box we hid. Want to know?

304
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,640
-Of course I do.
-Then what do we have to do?

305
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,600
You have to open it!

306
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:40,640
Let's open it!

307
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:48,280
-Here, hold it.
-Got it.

308
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:51,360
What is it? Drumroll!

309
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,360
Ta-da!

310
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,600
Whoa!

311
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,280
-What?
-Take a look!

312
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:02,120
-Drugs? No way!
-Oh no!

313
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:07,000
Hey.

314
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,080
What are those two doing?

315
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,800
-Hurry! Let's go!
-Go!

316
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:15,520
-Our fingerprints!
-How did it even get here?

317
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,720
-Put it back!
-Put it back now, quickly!

318
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,360
-Whoa!
-Oh no!

319
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:21,760
Ptui!

320
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:23,160
If that's the case,

321
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,720
there must be a drug dealer
at the company.

322
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,480
-I think so.
-But who?

323
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:32,040
Could Mr. Singha be a drug dealer?

324
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:33,200
-Really?
-Oh no!

325
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,040
-Hey!
-Oh.

326
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:42,040
You two are way too nosy!

327
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:44,080
Huh?

328
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,280
-You're dead!
-Mr. Singha!

329
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:50,560
Where is he?

330
00:24:51,080 --> 00:24:53,000
Hey, they're gone!

331
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:55,000
Stop standing there. Go after them!

332
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,840
Oh, man!

333
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:58,880
Run, quick!

334
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,040
-Village head! Don't ask now!
-Where are you going?

335
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,320
Someone's trying to shoot at us!

336
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,600
-Hurry! Move!
-Go! Run!

337
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,960
Hey, stop!

338
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,880
-Go after them!
-Hey!

339
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:28,960
Chart.

340
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,400
You saw what happened, right?

341
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,480
Anyone who knows about this,

342
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,440
make sure you get rid of them.

343
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,040
-Let's hide here.
-Okay.

344
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,400
-Oh no!
-Hey.

345
00:25:55,080 --> 00:25:56,120
What happened?

346
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:59,520
Drugs! They're drug dealers!

347
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,800
Who's dealing drugs?

348
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:03,080
Who else, Village Head?

349
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,920
The ones trying to kill us, of course!

350
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:09,640
We're done for! Run! Hurry!

351
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,800
You're dead!

352
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,120
-Where did they go?
-Geez!

353
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,680
Go after them!

354
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,880
Run!

355
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:25,320
-Joey, look out for yourself!
-Huh?

356
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,280
Hey! How can you just leave me?
You said you loved me!

357
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:30,120
Wait for me! Whoa!

358
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,960
Where did she go?

359
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:37,040
You know the secret.
Your punishment is death!

360
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:40,600
Honestly, I didn't mean to.
I was just walking around,

361
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,080
-looking up at the power lines…
-Hey!

362
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:43,120
Ouch!

363
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:51,560
-Ouch!
-Help!

364
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,480
What do we do now?

365
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:05,800
Don't let me catch you!

366
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,600
-Here, let me help you.
-Thank you.

367
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,760
Here you go. Thanks.

368
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,400
Puna, Chaiya!

369
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:26,480
Wow, that was amazing!

370
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:29,120
Hey, you've got
the talent of a real artist!

371
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:33,680
Absolutely. I can't believe
you did so well!

372
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,720
The views are skyrocketing,

373
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,920
and the likes are through the roof too!

374
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:41,120
But what you did is an insult to me!

375
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,880
How could you go on stage
instead of me, you brat?

376
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,000
Stop!

377
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:50,440
Not your business. Stay out of it!
We're from different companies.

378
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:53,200
Mr. Sonrak, why are you mad at me?
Did I do something wrong?

379
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:55,880
You're just a driver!
How could you go on stage instead of me?

380
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:01,960
Even if it were a street sweeper
or a dishwasher,

381
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:04,360
if they have a good voice,
I'd put them on stage.

382
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:09,080
Because I'm the one
responsible for the schedule.

383
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,760
If you didn't want Chaiya on stage,

384
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,320
why didn't you come sooner?

385
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:16,960
Honestly, you should even be thanking him

386
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,560
for helping fix the situation.

387
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,880
You should be thanking us.

388
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,320
Your show was so dull!

389
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:27,920
And you needed Darathong's driver
to save it.

390
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:31,200
Sorry, Maria.

391
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:33,840
Chaiya and Puna's views just now

392
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,240
were the highest of the day.

393
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:38,880
And most importantly,
the likes have gone up four or five times.

394
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,320
At this point,
is it even fair to call it dull?

395
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:45,000
Mr. Sonrak.

396
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:47,240
You were late today,

397
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:49,280
way past the scheduled time.

398
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,360
Do you still want to perform?

399
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:53,280
Are you threatening Mr. Sonrak?

400
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:55,880
I'm not threatening him,

401
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:58,440
but as the one responsible for the show,

402
00:28:58,520 --> 00:29:00,000
if someone isn't ready,

403
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:01,800
I can't let them go on stage.

404
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:11,360
I don't want to make a fuss.

405
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:16,400
Chaiya, you're part of the company.

406
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:19,120
Before doing anything,
shouldn't you have consulted me?

407
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,040
I didn't expect this.
It all happened so suddenly.

408
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:27,560
I'm sorry.

409
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,640
The next performers need to get ready.

410
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,640
Who should go on stage, Prae?

411
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:39,800
We're here. Let us go on now.

412
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:45,440
Alright, hurry and get ready.
Don't let there be any problems,

413
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,960
or I'll have to skip your turn.

414
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:52,280
Let's go, Mr. Sonrak.
We have to get ready.

415
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:16,720
STUDIO SEVEN

416
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:20,320
Back at the old company,
you never got to release a song.

417
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:23,840
But the moment
you moved to the new company,

418
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:26,400
you got one immediately.

419
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:31,800
I don't know
what had to be exchanged for that.

420
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,280
That's just how it is.

421
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:38,400
Some people are willing
to trade everything,

422
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,040
even themselves.

423
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,360
From what you said,

424
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,760
if you mean me,

425
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,840
you've got it wrong.

426
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,600
Someone like me
doesn't need to trade anything,

427
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,520
except my talent.

428
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,400
Then I'll be watching

429
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,640
to see just how far

430
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,680
your talent can take you.

431
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,280
What are you doing?

432
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:20,920
No one's checking your outfit, right?

433
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,680
See? This isn't tidy.

434
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:28,120
Tidy it properly.

435
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,000
You'll embarrass yourself on stage.

436
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:38,360
Puna.

437
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:43,240
It's almost time for the show.
Go on standby.

438
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:47,800
Wait, Puna. Puna!

439
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:55,920
The song's almost over.
Go wait by the side of the stage.

440
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,960
Okay.

441
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:02,640
Wow, Mr. Singer!

442
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:06,440
Hey, you were just on stage
singing a moment ago.

443
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:08,000
Switched to photography now?

444
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:10,440
Stop teasing me.

445
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,440
Hey, I'm serious. You should quit.

446
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:16,280
Become a singer.
You've got real potential!

447
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:19,400
Don't distract me.

448
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,240
Has Captain Tom sent any news yet?

449
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:24,160
Oh, right. Let me check.

450
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,320
-Have you been here long?
-Just arrived, sir.

451
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:35,960
Which car is the target?

452
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:38,880
That's the target car, parked right there.

453
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:40,440
What's the plan?

454
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,400
Wait until Sonrak
finishes his performance,

455
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:45,480
-then request a search.
-Understood.

456
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:48,320
Corporal Chom, in the meantime,
have the undercover officers

457
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:50,640
tail Sonrak. Don't let him get away.

458
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:51,560
Understood, Captain.

459
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,920
That's central police.

460
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:04,920
The captain's causing trouble again.

461
00:33:10,760 --> 00:33:13,320
Those two moved the stuff
into Village Head Prueng's car.

462
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,960
Then just put it back where it was.

463
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,760
But I've got a plan.

464
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:39,920
-All set?
-All set, bro.

465
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,640
-Let's go.
-Yes.

466
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:50,240
So those are the drug boxes.

467
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:53,400
Sneaky little devils.

468
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:22,400
<i>Take my heart for your consideration</i>

469
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:25,800
<i>Check it out and see</i>

470
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:29,639
<i>If my heart is new or old</i>

471
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:35,679
<i>Is it broken? Is there any damage?</i>

472
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:39,560
<i>Or are there any cracks</i>

473
00:34:39,639 --> 00:34:42,679
<i>Glued over to hide the truth?</i>

474
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:49,280
<i>The four chambers of my heart</i>
<i>Are still brand new</i>

475
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:53,280
<i>True and genuine, not fake or false</i>

476
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:57,120
<i>No tricks, no schemes</i>

477
00:34:57,680 --> 00:35:02,920
<i>Only overflowing love</i>
<i>Filling every corner of my heart</i>

478
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:06,560
<i>I'm willing to give it to you</i>

479
00:35:06,640 --> 00:35:10,880
<i>Please accept it and consider</i>

480
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:14,120
<i>When will you accept?</i>

481
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:18,160
<i>When will you know?</i>

482
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:23,880
<i>If you already have a love</i>
<i>Please, hurry and tell me</i>

483
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:31,400
<i>If you're still single</i>
<i>I beg you, with kindness</i>

484
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:37,960
<i>Take a little time to consider my heart</i>

485
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:44,680
<i>I offer you my heart</i>
<i>Waiting for your answer</i>

486
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:47,640
<i>I'm ready for you to test it</i>

487
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:52,400
<i>Inside the chamber of my heart</i>

488
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:57,840
<i>If you still see the value in my goodness</i>

489
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:01,360
<i>I'm ready to give my life</i>

490
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:05,960
<i>If you consider it</i>

491
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:12,160
Hey, this looks great. Perfect!

492
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:17,880
Hey, Corporal Chom.

493
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:21,000
The captain sent me to tail Mr. Sonrak.

494
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,920
You saw the photos I sent, right?
They're in the box in the back seat.

495
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,200
Yes.

496
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:32,000
There are two of them,
Tod and Wong.

497
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,440
They're likely the ones
delivering the goods.

498
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:38,600
Got it. I'll report back to the captain.

499
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:41,520
Corporal.

500
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:43,680
Step back a bit.
They might get suspicious.

501
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:45,320
Okay. I'm sorry.

502
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:50,080
Chaiya, I'll check
that everything's ready by the stage.

503
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:53,240
Go ahead. Nothing else to do here.

504
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:03,400
Hey, Sergeant. Any news?

505
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,840
Captain Tom contacted central police.

506
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:09,800
That means your info leaked.

507
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:12,240
Leaked? How?

508
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,080
Who told them?

509
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:18,040
Could it be you, Chart?

510
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,320
Me? No way.

511
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,240
I've been working with you
for a long time.

512
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:24,160
I'd never betray you.

513
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:29,480
Then cancel today's plan.
Don't take any risks

514
